Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @tomato{1}. Trim and finely dice @radishes{3}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Drain and rinse @black beans{1}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, radishes, scallion greens, half the cilantro, and @white wine vinegar{1%tsp}. (Reserve remaining @white wine vinegar{4%tsp} for another use.) Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper, scallion whites, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in beans, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, and @water{2%tbsp}. Cook until beans are warmed through and water has absorbed, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} until melted (save the Monterey Jack for serving).

Divide lettuce leaves between plates. Fill with bean filling. Top with salsa, @sour cream{3%tbsp}, @guacamole{4%tbsp}, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and remaining cilantro. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.